    <h1>8.1.4 Data Analysis Engine: Item Level Security</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h2 id=3D"id-8.1.4DataAnalysisEngine:ItemLevelSecurity-Sharing">Sha=
ring</h2>
<p>The only point in sharing a DAD is to allow other users to collaborate o=
n the development of the DAD. All consequences of the existance of a DAD ot=
her than webnotifications (emails, records written, http requests) are "use=
able" by other users just as much as by the creator the DAD.&nbsp;</p>
<p>We suspect that sharing DAD's is functionality that will be seldomly use=
d and is low priority.&nbsp;</p>
<p><span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=3D"1d77c183-ce0b-4aef-bd8=
0-936f68fe929d">There are also some issues with sharing a DAD: suppose A sh=
ares a DAD with B. B adds a clause to the DAD stating that he'd like to rec=
eive notifications. However, only the owner of a DAD receives notifications=
, not all of the people the DAD is shared with. So A, instead of B, would r=
eceive these notifications, thereby confusing both A and B.</span>&nbsp;</p=
>
<p>As a result, we chose not to implement DAD sharing.&nbsp;</p>
<h2 id=3D"id-8.1.4DataAnalysisEngine:ItemLevelSecurity-Transferofownership"=
>Transfer of ownership</h2>
<p>Transfer of ownership should be available for all RAS objects, including=
 DAD's. When a DAD is transferred from one user to the next, the system sho=
uld check if the new user has access to all of the mentioned assets. &nbsp;=
When transferring ownership, a rabbitmq message should be sent to the DAE n=
otifying it that the owner has changed. The DAE will then reload the DAD wi=
thout recalculation.&nbsp;</p>
<p>We considered making it so that if the receiving user does not have acce=
ss to all assets mentioned in the latest version of the DAD, the user shoul=
d not be able to accept the transfer of ownership. However, if the new owne=
r does not have the required access to the asset, the DAD will disable itse=
lf and log an error. Therefore, notifying beforehand is not required.&nbsp;=
</p>
<h2 id=3D"id-8.1.4DataAnalysisEngine:ItemLevelSecurity-Usage">Usage</h2>
<h3 id=3D"id-8.1.4DataAnalysisEngine:ItemLevelSecurity-Readingdata">Reading=
 data</h3>
<p>A DAD should only be able to read the things his owner can read, and to =
write to places the owner can write. As such, we need to check whether any =
asset referenced (either by id or by name) is managed by the DAD owner's co=
mpany.</p>
<p>Furthermore, we need to ensure that the IDE auto-suggest only provides t=
he properties for assets that are managed by the DAD's owner's company. If =
we were to forget to implement this check, you could use the autosuggest fu=
nctionality to retrieve a list of properties for any asset, even ones you h=
ave no affiliation with. This information in turn&nbsp; could be used by a =
smart attacker to determine asset types, and could even be used to build an=
 entire database of all asset ID's that are in use and their corresponding =
properties.&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"id-8.1.4DataAnalysisEngine:ItemLevelSecurity-Writingdata">Writing=
 data</h3>
<p>Currently, we do not have a separate permission for writing new data to =
the database. All users are able to set (static) parameters for all assets =
managed by their companies. Similarly, all DAD's can write new data to the =
database provided the parametername starts with "<span class=3D"inline-comm=
ent-marker" data-ref=3D"1efc8ad3-16c1-4583-b8e3-fb6777e4e219">DAE_</span>".=
&nbsp; All records that are written to the database by the DAE should be ma=
rked as such in the database.&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"id-8.1.4DataAnalysisEngine:ItemLevelSecurity-Emails">Emails</h3>
<p>Emails can be sent to all <span class=3D"inline-comment-marker" data-ref=
=3D"84defa25-6be2-4eab-bd75-de5ef3e34940">e-mail addresses</span>, irrespec=
tive of DAD owner. No checks are necessary.&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"id-8.1.4DataAnalysisEngine:ItemLevelSecurity-Webnotifications">We=
bnotifications</h3>
<p>Webnotifications are always sent to the DAD owner, so no checks are nece=
ssary.&nbsp;</p>
<h3 id=3D"id-8.1.4DataAnalysisEngine:ItemLevelSecurity-HTTPRequests">HTTP R=
equests</h3>
<p>HTTP requests too are independent of DAD owner, so no checks are necessa=
ry.&nbsp;</p>
<p><br></p>
